                ParagraphText="Observe and measure the pressure ulcer.  Categorize the ulcer with respect to surface area, exudate and type of wound tissue.  Record a sub-score for each of these ulcer characteristics.  Add the sub-scores to obtain the total score.  A comparison to total scores measured over time provides an indication of the improvement or deterioration in pressure ulcer healing."
